               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the original owners; titles of the Gospels; the incipit lines of headings and chapters; chapter numbers and the word mǝˤǝraf; punctuation signs and/or their elements; elements of Ethiopic numerals within the text.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- Biography of John is misplaced (fol. 17<ref type="mss" corresp="ES4ra174">4ra-174</ref>va). Usually it comes before the Bǝsratä Yoḥannǝs “The Gospel of John”.</note>
                     <note>- The “Tituli” for the Gospels of Mark and John are not numbered.</note>
                     <note>- There are 44 “Tituli” for the Gospel of Mark (usually 48) and 19 for the Gospel of John (usually 20).</note>
                     <note>- The canon tables are missing.</note>
                     <note>- The scribe always uses a line break after the number of the chapter before its incipit.</note>
                  </msItem>
