               <person>
                  <persName role="owner" corresp="PRS0000">ʾAto Wäldä ʾArägawi is mentioned as the donor in Additio 1 and in the supplication formula on fol. 3rb.&#xD;
Also his family members are mentioned.</persName>
                  <!--ACHTUNG! This is actually paragraphic information identifying the donor. 
                                        Person/persName should only contain the person name, not all the paragraph.-->
               </person>
               <person>
                  <persName role="scribe" corresp="PRS00000">Wagris</persName>
               </person>
               <person>
                  <persName role="owner" corresp="PRS0000">The first owner of the Ms. was probably King Yoḥannǝs I (r. 1667-82) since his name, his mother’s (?) name ʾƎḫǝtä Krǝstos and his wife’s name Säblä Wängel are mentioned in the headings of the Gospel of Mark (s. fol. 52rb), Luke (fol. 81rb) and John (fol. 134rb). Probably, their names were also written in the heading of the Mathews Gospel but later erased (fol. 3rb) in order to write down the name of the later donor, ʾato Wäldä ʾArägawi.&#xD;
Another possibility is that the commissioner of the Ms. only wished to mention the name of the ruler.  &#xD;
Later, the Ms. belonged to the church of Mäqdäla Mädḫane ʿAläm.</persName>
                  <!--ACHTUNG! This is actually paragraphic information identifying the donor. 
                                        Person/persName should only contain the person name, not all the paragraph.-->
               </person>
